\c[0]It's covered in graffiti.
\bSuntouched City has multiple levels.
\bOne is on the ground, and the other is way up in the clouds.
\bYou can use the fan to travel between the levels.
\rAre you here to challenge the Gym?
\rYou'll have to go to the cloud layer to do that.
\rJust hop on the fan there! I promise- it's perfectly safe!
\bOrion's a very tricky Gym Leader to face.\nHe's supposed to be a Fire-type leader... but that's not the only type I've seen him use!
\bThat big red and black building is the Subway Station.
\bI heard it can take you to any region in the entire world!
\bI'm saving up for a trip to Hoenn!\nOoh, or maybe Sinnoh! Or Aroma!
\bI don't know how they let Orion lead this city's Gym.
\bHe talks to rocks in his spare time!
\bI'm sorry, but the Pokemon Subway Station is currently cordoned off to the public.
\bI'm sorry, but the Pokemon Subway Station is currently-
\bOh, I see! You're with Professor Pine! Good to know.
\bFirst door to the left in the building.
\bThe train to Holon leaves right away.
\bWelcome back, Augur!
\bFirst door to the left in the building.
\bThe train to Holon leaves right away.
\rI once heard there was someone in Helios City who sells an item that lets you evolve Pokemon that evolve by trading.
\rI went to Helios City to evolve my Haunter...
\rBut I couldn't find the guy! He must have been underground.
\bYou need the Thermal Badge to cross water.
\bThat means that if you want to travel to the south, you'll have to beat our Gym Leader first!
\bCertain Pokemon need a stone to evolve.
\bA Moon Stone will allow you to evolve certain Pokemon like Clefairy.
A
Kernel.pbReceiveItem(PBItems::MOONSTONE)
A
\bI hope that helps you!
\bSuntouched City is the media center of the region.
\bFrom here, we make movies and broadcast TV shows to all over the region!
\rMy favourite Pokemon is Jigglypuff! If you show me one, I'll give you something cool!
pbHasSpecies?(PBSpecies::JIGGLYPUFF)
\rYou have a Jigglypuff!\nThank's for showing it to me!
\rYou should have these!
Kernel.pbReceiveItem(PBItems::HEARTSCALE,2)
A
\rMy favourite Pokemon is Jigglypuff!
pbCaveExit
\bThat's one huge statue!\nIt's only fitting- a great statue for a wondrous man!
\bNot gonna lie, I helped with the vandalism of the Augur's statue. I'm positively disgusted by what he did.
\r\pn. Thank you for coming.
\rIt's been a while, hasn't it?
\rI must say, the Scientist's Club definitely isn't as active as the rest of them.
\rI might just disband it, honestly. There isn't much left you can help us out with.
\rBut this one! Oh, man. This is huge.
\rRecently, our scientists have made a huge discovery.
\rDelta Species... in other regions.
\rI know, right? Isn't that amazing?
\rNot only that... but researchers believe that this might be the region that Delta Species originated from!
\rThat's right- the Holon Region! You might have heard of it before.
\rNobody really knows where they came from- some ancient civilization, some energy wave, maybe even just Darwinian mutation.
\rBut that's what you're here for!
\rI'd like to cordially invite you to join us over in the Holon Region.
\rThe guards will let you through if you say you're with me.\nBefore you know it you'll be on a path to a whole new region, filled to the brim with Delta Pokemon!
\rThese aren't traditional Deltas either. The ones you'll find in Holon have all been discovered, so to speak, by guest researchers at the Holon University.
\rSo to speak. I hope you get what I mean.
\rThe researchers who discovered them will be recorded in their dex entries.
\rAnyways! Please!
\rI'll see you in Holon! I know another Professor- Maple- who would love to make your acquaintance.
